speaker: DOCTOR
transcribe: Well, okay, good afternoon. I'm Dr. [PERSON_NAME]. I'm on duty here at the Emergency Department and Hospital. I need to make sure that you are aware that you are in hospital.

transcribe: Sì, ma non capisco perché sono ancora qui, perché mi sento bene. Yes, [PERSON_NAME] don't understand why I feel fine.

speaker: DOCTOR
transcribe: I recommend that you stay in hospital for [DATE], observations, tests.

transcribe: Certainly. Now I understand that you may feel fine but the paramedics and doctors observed some symptoms. transcribe: I had a dizzy spell. Now I'm on holiday in [PERSON_NAME] with my wife. We are on an organized tour with 11 people. transcribe: Well now, I'm really sorry but I need to go now. I will ask the nurse to book an appointment for you for more tests and I will look at the results when they come in.
